    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">813.00/1108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Honduran Minister of Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Uclés</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I thank you for your telegram of September 12 in which you inform me on behalf of
                    the Provisional Federal Council of the Republic <pb facs="0282" n="158"
                        xml:id="pg_158"/> of Central America that the National Constituent Assembly
                    signed the political constitution of the new Republic on September 11. I beg you
                    to convey to the Provisional Federal Council of the Republic of Central America
                    my sincere felicitations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
